# MSTR ACL AUDIT — Full Coverage, Production Ready

Version : 3.0

WHAT THIS SCRIPT DOES:
Connects to 3 MicroStrategy servers (DEV / UAT / PROD), loops through all
projects on each server and produces a complete access control audit covering:
- Who is a member of each project (User Manager / Project Membership)
- Who has ACL rights on the project object itself
- Who has ACL rights on every folder (Public Objects, Schema Objects,
and all child folders) down to depth 7
- Full inheritance chain — direct vs inherited per folder

COVERAGE:
✅ Project membership  — groups/users added via User Manager
✅ Project-level ACL   — rights on the project object itself
✅ Public Objects      — root + all subfolders to depth 7
✅ Schema Objects      — root + Attributes, Facts, Hierarchies, Tables, etc.
✅ All predefined root folders
✅ AD/LDAP groups (trusteeSubtype 8705)
✅ Individual users directly assigned (trusteeSubtype 8704)
✅ Paginated folder reads — no contents silently truncated
✅ Inheritance chain tracked at every level
✅ SSL verify=False, urllib3 warnings suppressed

OUTPUTS (written to ./mstr_acl_output/):

1. dev_context.json / uat_context.json / prod_context.json  — RAG-ready JSON
1. dev_ai_context.md / uat_ai_context.md / prod_ai_context.md — LLM markdown
1. all_environments_acl.csv   — flat CSV, all decoded fields, all 3 envs
1. project_membership.csv     — who is a project member across all 3 envs
1. mstr_acl_audit.log         — full run log

